contract.name: Brooklyn :: Test 1
contract.description: I must not fear. Fear is the mind-killer. Fear is the little-death that brings total obliteration. I will face my fear. I will permit it to pass over me and through me. And when it has gone past I will turn the inner eye to see its path. Where the fear has gone there will be nothing. Only I will remain.

details: The mystery of life isn't a problem to solve, but a reality to experience.
It is impossible to live in the past, difficult to live in the present and a waste to live in the future.
